Parser

Extends \PhpParser\ParserAbstract

package

Default

Methods

Creates a parser instance.

__construct(\PhpParser\Lexer $lexer, array $options = array())
inherited

Arguments

$lexer

\PhpParser\Lexer

A lexer

$options

array

Options array. The boolean 'throwOnError' option determines whether an exception should be thrown on first error, or if the parser should try to continue parsing the remaining code and build a partial AST.

getErrorMessage

getErrorMessage( $symbol,  $state)
inherited

Arguments

$symbol

$state

Get array of errors that occurred during the last parse.

getErrors() : array<mixed,\PhpParser\Error>
inherited

This method may only return multiple errors if the 'throwOnError' option is disabled.

Response

array<mixed,\PhpParser\Error>

getExpectedTokens

getExpectedTokens( $state)
inherited

Arguments

$state

getNamespacingStyle

getNamespacingStyle(array $stmts)
inherited

Arguments

$stmts

array

Moves statements of semicolon-style namespaces into $ns->stmts and checks various error conditions.

handleNamespaces(array<mixed,\PhpParser\Node> $stmts) : array<mixed,\PhpParser\Node>
inherited

Arguments

$stmts

array<mixed,\PhpParser\Node>

Response

array<mixed,\PhpParser\Node>

Parses PHP code into a node tree.

parse(string $code) : array<mixed,\PhpParser\Node>|null
inherited

Arguments

$code

string

The source code to parse

Response

array<mixed,\PhpParser\Node>|null

Array of statements (or null if the 'throwOnError' option is disabled and the parser was unable to recover from an error).

Table indexed analogously to $action. If $actionCheck[$actionBase[$state] + $symbol] != $symbol then the action is defaulted, i.e. $actionDefault[$state] should be used instead.

Map of states to a displacement into the $action table. The corresponding action for this state/symbol pair is $action[$actionBase[$state] + $symbol]. If $actionBase[$state] is 0, the action is defaulted, i.e. $actionDefault[$state] should be used instead.
